msgctxt "title"
msgid "Breathe, Think, Do with Sesame"
msgstr "Respira, piensa, actúa con Sésamo"

msgctxt "blurb"
msgid ""
"\"Help a monster friend with big feelings learn to calm down and solve everyday challenges.\" Yes please! Elmo and the gang at Sesame Street's app -- aimed at parents and caregivers of kids aged 2-5"
" -- is designed to help the young ones learn how to calm down, learn self-control, and expand their emotional vocabulary. The app is bilingual in English and Spanish, research-based, and free to "
"download and use. Sesame Workshop's<a id=\"a1\"> privacy polic</a>y says most of the things kids can do on the app don't require users to submit any personal information. Yay! Now, if they only made"
" an adult version too! Unfortunately, we do have some small security concerns about the app."
msgstr ""
"«Ayuda a un monstruo amigo con grandes sentimientos a aprender a calmarse y resolver desafíos diarios». ¡Sí, por favor! Elmo y su pandilla están en la aplicación de Plaza Sésamo: dirigida a padres y"
" cuidadores de niños de 2 a 5 años, ha sido diseñada para ayudar a los más pequeños a aprender a calmarse, a descubrir el autocontrol y a ampliar su vocabulario emocional. La aplicación es bilingüe,"
" en inglés y español, tiene bases científicas y se puede descargar y usar de forma gratuita. La<a id=\"a1\"> política de privacida</a>d de Sesame Workshop dice que la mayoría de las actividades que "
"pueden hacer los niños en la aplicación no requiere el envío de ninguna información personal. ¡Hurra! ¡Cómo me gustaría que hicieran también una versión para adultos! Aunque, desafortunadamente, "
"tenemos algunas pequeñas preocupaciones de seguridad sobre la aplicación."

msgctxt "worst_case"
msgid ""
"We're not too worried about the privacy of Sesame Workshop's mental development app for young children. TThe privacy policy does say that sometimes personal information like name and email might be "
"collected but only with parental consent. And with no behavioral advertising (read, targeted ads) on the platform, parents should be able to breathe a small sigh of relief. Sesame Workshop is an "
"educational non-profit, so they aren't trying to make money off you or your child's data, which is a breath of fresh air."
msgstr ""
"No nos preocupa demasiado la privacidad de la aplicación de desarrollo cognitivo de Sesame Workshop para niños pequeños. Su política de privacidad dice que en ocasiones se pueden recopilar datos "
"personales como el nombre y el correo electrónico, pero solo con el consentimiento de los padres. Además, en la plataforma no hay publicidad conductual (léase, anuncios dirigidos), lo que permite a "
"los padres dar un pequeño suspiro de alivio. Sesame Workshop es una organización educativa sin fines de lucro, por lo que no están tratando de ganar dinero con tus datos o los de tus hijos... un "
"soplo de aire fresco."

msgctxt "worst_case"
msgid ""
"Our biggest privacy flag for this app is the privacy policy hasn't been updated since 2013, which is a very long time in privacy policy years. All in all though, if parents <a id=\"a1\">follow</a> "
"the <a id=\"a2\">basic guidelines</a> for <a id=\"a3\">protecting</a> young children online (please always do this parents and caregivers!), your child's privacy will likely be pretty safe."
msgstr ""
"Nuestra mayor alerta con respecto a esta aplicación es que no han actualizado su política de privacidad desde 2013, lo que representa un periodo muy largo si lo pensamos en años de políticas de "
"privacidad. Sin embargo, en general, si los padres <a id=\"a1\">siguen</a> las pautas <a id=\"a2\">básicas</a> para <a id=\"a3\">proteger</a> a los pequeños en línea (¡hagan esto siempre, padres y "
"cuidadores!), es probable que la privacidad de tus hijos esté bastante segura."

msgctxt "worst_case"
msgid ""
"We do have some questions we couldn't get answered about the security of this app. We couldn't confirm if Sesame Workshop has a program to manage security vulnerabilities. We did reach out to ask "
"these questions to the email provided in their privacy policy, however we received no response. Which is concerning as this is also the email address provided for parents to contact Sesame Workshop "
"to have any potential child's personal information reviewed and/or removed. With an app that collects so little personal information, this is probably not too big a concern. However, the app does "
"request permission for access to a device's microphone, so an insecure app could be a problem."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "worst_case"
msgid ""
"What's the worst that could happen? Hopefully nothing more than your child learns how to be a little bit calmer. Calm is good. However, if the app were to have an unmanaged security vulnerability "
"that gave a bad person access to your phone's microphone without you knowing, well, that wouldn't be good at all. This is probably not likely to happen. But we should remind parents that anything "
"that connects to the internet your child plays with has potential vulnerabilities so it's always good to supervise them when they use your devices."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "how_does_it_use_data_collected"
msgid ""
"There is no behavioral advertising on the platform which means that you will not see any advertising that is targeted to you based on your combined activity on the platform and your activity on "
"other sites and apps."
msgstr ""
"No hay publicidad conductual en la plataforma, esto significa que no verás publicidades dirigidas a ti en función de la combinación de tu actividad en la plataforma y en otros sitios y aplicaciones."

msgctxt "how_does_it_use_data_collected"
msgid "The app do not make personal information collected from children publicly available"
msgstr "La aplicación no pone a disposición del público la información personal recopilada de los niños"

msgctxt "how_does_it_use_data_collected"
msgid "The policy does not mention any sharing of data with third parties, or selling of data."
msgstr "La política no menciona ningún intercambio de datos con terceros, ni la venta de datos."

msgctxt "uses_encryption_helptext"
msgid "The app collects no personal data"
msgstr "La aplicación no recopila ningún dato personal"

msgctxt "strong_password_helptext"
msgid "No password needed, as there is no sign-up process in the app"
msgstr "No se necesita contraseña, ya que no hay proceso de registro en la aplicación"

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Parents should <a id=\"a1\">read up</a> and <a id=\"a2\">implement the guidelines</a> on how to protect children online."
msgstr "Los padres deben <a id=\"a1\">leer</a> e <a id=\"a2\">implementar las pautas</a> sobre cómo proteger a los niños en línea."

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Never share your child's personal information online"
msgstr "Nunca compartas la información personal de tus hijos en línea"

msgctxt "tips_to_protect_yourself"
msgid "Use the app with your child"
msgstr "Utiliza la aplicación junto con tu hijo(a)"

msgctxt "personal_data_collected"
msgid "Optional: name, email, phone number. Most of the activities on the Platforms do not require you to submit any personal information."
msgstr "Opcional: nombre, correo electrónico, número de teléfono. La mayoría de las actividades en las plataformas no requieren que envíes ningún dato personal."

msgctxt "how_can_you_control_your_data"
msgid ""
"Parents may contact the provider at dotorgmail@sesameworkshop.org to review, update or delete any of their children’s personal information that the app may have collected and to elect for the app "
"not to collect any additional personal information from their children."
msgstr ""
"Los padres pueden ponerse en contacto con el proveedor a través de dotorgmail@ses.shop.org para revisar, actualizar o eliminar cualquier dato personal de sus hijos que la aplicación pueda haber "
"recopilado, y para determinar que la aplicación no recopile ninguna información personal adicional de sus hijos."

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid "No known privacy or security incidents discovered in the last 3 years."
msgstr "No se han conocido incidentes de privacidad o seguridad en los últimos 3 años."

msgctxt "child_safety_blurb"
msgid ""
"The app's collection of personal information on Platforms that are directed to children under 13 is intended to follow the principles of the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act, a U.S. law "
"designed to protect the online privacy of children under the age of 13. The app will obtain parental consent before asking for personal information on the Children’s Platforms, unless the request "
"for information falls within an exception that would be permitted under COPPA."
msgstr ""
